Here's the approach:

### 1. Define theme ResourceDictionaries

Create separate XAML files for each theme:

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextPrimary">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Repeat for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with different values but **the same keys**.

### 2. Create a ThemeService

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string themeName)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove the current theme dictionary (always the last one added)
        var existing = mergedDicts.FirstOrDefault(d => d.Source?.OriginalString.Contains("Theme") == true);
        if (existing is not null)
            mergedDicts.Remove(existing);

        var theme = themeName switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast"  => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _              => new LightTheme(),
        };

        mergedDicts.Add(theme);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", themeName);
    }
}
```

### 3. Wire it up at startup (`App.xaml.cs`)

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light");
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(saved);
}
```

### 4. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker Title="Theme" SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged">
    <Picker.ItemsSource>
        <x:Array Type="{x:Type x:String}">
            <x:String>Light</x:String>
            <x:String>Dark</x:String>
            <x:String>HighContrast</x:String>
        </x:Array>
    </Picker.ItemsSource>
</Picker>
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (sender is Picker p && p.SelectedItem is string theme)
        ThemeService.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

### 5. Consume theme colors with `DynamicResource`

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource TextPrimary}" Text="Hello!" />
</ContentPage>
```

> **Key point:** Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) so controls pick up changes immediately when you swap the dictionary at runtime.

### Quick checklist

| Concern | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| Immediate switch | `MergedDictionaries` swap + `DynamicResource` |
| Persistence | `Preferences.Set` / `Preferences.Get` |
| Consistency | All three dictionaries share identical keys |
| High-contrast a11y | Use strongly contrasting colors & thicker borders in that dictionary |
